    "narrative": "Today\u2019s slate for the Austin Waves is anchored by high-ceiling matchups against pitchers with elevated xERAs, led by **Kyle Tucker** (85.72) and **Gunnar Henderson** (80.97). **Kyle Tucker** is our premier play, benefiting from a +14% park factor boost and an ideal leadoff spot against Sugano, while **Gunnar Henderson** maintains a robust score through a dynamic platoon advantage and high-volume opportunities at the top of the order. Meanwhile, **Andy Pages** (75.57) and **Drake Baldwin** (72.00) represent significant value plays; **Andy Pages** gains massive leverage from the park environment, and **Drake Baldwin** faces a vulnerable arm in Walker, with his batting order placement at #2 providing a substantial efficiency lift.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was excluding **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (60.17). While he remains an elite talent with a strong xwOBA, his projected efficiency fell just short of our utility threshold compared to **Marcell Ozuna** (60.53). The optimizer favored **Marcell Ozuna** due to a slightly more favorable SP skill matchup, whereas **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** faced the drag of a neutral platoon and a tougher assignment against Soroka. We are also keeping a close eye on **Luis Robert Jr.** (50.66) and **Brady House** (47.56); while both possess the speed profiles we covet for our scarcity-driven strategy, their raw projections were suppressed today by tough matchups against Logan Webb and Edward Cabrera, forcing us to prioritize safer floor options to maximize daily utility.\n\nRisk remains prevalent today due to the sheer volume of \"Lineup Pending\" statuses, specifically surrounding **Nolan Schanuel**, **Jacob Wilson**, **Miguel Vargas**, **Josh Lowe**, **Kyle Tucker**, and **Jackson Merrill**. Should any of these players move down in their respective orders once confirmed, their daily scores will require immediate re-evaluation. Additionally, while **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (56.01) is a start, we are cautious of his matchup against Logan Webb, whose elite skill level (-19% impact) drags down what would otherwise be a much higher efficiency score. We will monitor weather and final lineup cards closely to ensure no unexpected scratches force a rotation shift for the Waves.",
